result.execSummary:
The defendant William C Maysack was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Take (<=$500), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant William C Maysack in court with attorney Thomas K Hackbart.  Defendant William C Maysack in custody.  Taylor L. Kraus appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  

Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Court sentenced defendant to serve 20 DAYS in the House of Correction with credit for 20 days served FOR A TIME SERVED DISPOSITION.

Court ordered defendant to pay ALL COSTS and SURCHARGES by 03-02-2017 or, as a penalty if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.  Appeal rights given.
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.

Attorney Thomas K Hackbart in court, defendant William C Maysack not in court, in custody.  Taylor L. Kraus appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  Filed, State's Motion in Limine, State's Requested Jury Instructions and State's Witness List.  Final pretrial held.  Case remains calendared for jury trial on March 2, 2016 at 8:30 am in Branch 21.

Attorney Thomas K. Hackbart in court, defendant William C Maysack not in court, in custody.  Daniel J. Gabler appeared for the State of Wisconsin. CMC. Defense requests Final Pretrial and Jury Trial dates. Court grants defense request.   Parties are advised that effective December 14, 2015, this case will be assigned to the Reserve Judge presiding in Branch 21 in room 622 of the Courthouse. Case adjourned to branch 21.  Final pre-trial scheduled for February 2, 2016 at 08:30 am.  Jury trial scheduled for March 2, 2016 at 08:30 am.

Attorney Thomas K. Hackbart in court, defendant William C Maysack not in court, in custody.  Joy Hammond appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  The defendant was not produced from Oshkosh Correctional.    Court ordered case adjourned for projected guilty plea in Branch 24.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for December 1, 2015 at 01:30 pm.

Attorney Thomas K. Hackbart in court, defendant William C Maysack not in court, in custody.  Joy Hammond appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  Defense counsel advised the Court that the defendant has several pending matters in other counties.  Court ordered case adjourned for projected guilty plea in Branch 24.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for November 10, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
COURT ORDERED DEFENDANT PRODUCED FROM DODGE FOR PURPOSES OF THE PROJECTED GUILTY PLEA AND SENTENCING IN BRANCH 24.

Attorney Thomas K. Hackbart in court, Defendant William C Maysack not in court, in custody.  Joy Hammond appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant not produced from Dodge for purposes of this hearing.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for October 6, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with TARGET, 7800 S. LOVER'S LANE RD., FRANKLIN, WI 53132.
  Court advised defendant that failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Court orders defendant TURNED OVER to JUSTICE Point for Supervision to be monitored by drug testing.
   Court ordered no possession or use of controlled substances without a valid prescription.

Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to defendant's attorney.  Defendant plead not guilty.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND QUALIFIES FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION.

Defendant William C Maysack in court with attorney Calvin R. Malone.  Defendant William C Maysack in custody.  Ronald Dague appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk:  hgj.  Request for Substitution of Judge received and filed.  Court consented to substitution against Judge SIEFERT.  Parties are advised the Clerk of Circuit Court reassigned case pursuant to current court rules to Judge PROTASIEWICZ, Br. 24.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for August 27, 2015 at 08:30 am.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
Arrest Warrant received from the D.A.'s office on filing date of Criminal Complaint.
